    {
      "id": "jshell-101-strings-md",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## String Operations\n\n`String` in Java is **immutable** — every operation that appears to modify a string actually returns a *new* String. This makes strings safe to share across the program but means you should avoid building strings with `+` in a loop (use `StringBuilder` for that).\n\nCommon methods to know: `length()`, `charAt()`, `substring()`, `toUpperCase()`, `toLowerCase()`, `trim()`, `contains()`, `replace()`, `split()`, `startsWith()`, `endsWith()`.",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "jshell-101-strings",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "//@ anchor: string-operations\n//@ description: String operations\n// --- String operations ---\nString message = \"  Hello, Arima Notebooks!  \";\n\n// Trimming whitespace\nString trimmed = message.trim();                        // \"Hello, Arima Notebooks!\"\nSystem.out.println(\"trimmed    : '\" + trimmed + \"'\");\n\n// Case conversion\nSystem.out.println(\"upper      : \" + trimmed.toUpperCase());\nSystem.out.println(\"lower      : \" + trimmed.toLowerCase());\n\n// Length and character access\nSystem.out.println(\"length     : \" + trimmed.length());          // 23\nSystem.out.println(\"charAt(7)  : \" + trimmed.charAt(7));         // 'V'\n\n// Substring: from index (inclusive) to index (exclusive)\nSystem.out.println(\"substring  : \" + trimmed.substring(7, 12)); // \"Arima\"\n\n// Searching and replacing\nSystem.out.println(\"contains 'Arima' : \" + trimmed.contains(\"Arima\"));\nSystem.out.println(\"replaced   : \" + trimmed.replace(\"Arima\", \"Java\"));\n\n// String.format for structured output\nString formatted = String.format(\"User: %-10s | Score: %05d\", \"Alice\", 42);\nSystem.out.println(formatted);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": "string-operations",
